wild ginger
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:One of two <i>Hedychium</i> spp., <i>gardnerianum</i> (kahili) and <i>flavescens</i> (yellow).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes: Name and plant known to me from 1950s. Now a serious pest plant. <i>Introduced Wildflowers, New Zealand Weeds</i>, Gordon Ell, Bush Press, 1983; <i>Native Forest Restoration</i>, Tim Porteous, QEII National Trust., 1993. NSOD and Collins record wild ginger as <i>NAmer</i> but with reference to a wholly different plant, <i>Avarum canadense</i>.
